<p class="main">State Agencies that Accredit Institutions</p>
<p class="mainsub">Finally, accreditation from these state agencies also meets InCommon's requirements. </p>
<ul>
  <li class="mainsub">New York State Board of Regents (Public Postsecondary Vocational Education), <a href="http://www.nysed.gov">http://www.nysed.gov</a></li>
  <li class="mainsub">Oklahoma Board of Career and Technology Education, <a href="http://www.okcareertech.org">http://www.okcareertech.org</a></li>
  <li class="mainsub">Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, <a href="http://www.okhighered.org">http://www.okhighered.org</a></li>
  <li class="mainsub">Pennsylvania State Board of Vocational Education, Bureau of Career and Technical Education, <a href="http://www.portal.state.pa.us/portal/server.pt/community/Career_&_Technical_Education/7335/">http://www.portal.state.pa.us/portal/server.pt/community/Career_&_Technical_Education/7335/</a></li>
  <li class="mainsub">Puerto Rico State Agency for the Approval of Public Postsecondary Vocational, Technical Institutions and Programs, <a href="http://www.de.gobierno.pr">http://www.de.gobierno.pr</a></li>
</ul></td>
